.TH qthread_retloc 3 "NOVEMBER 2006" libqthread "libqthread"
.SH NAME
\fBqthread_retloc\fR \- returns the qthread's unique ID number
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <qthread/qthread.h>

.I aligned_t *
.br
\fBqthread_retloc\fR(qthread_t *\fIt\fR);
.SH DESCRIPTION
This function returns the location that the return value of the qthread_t
\fIr\fR will be stored into, if one has been defined.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
If \fIt\fR is non-null, it returns a pointer to the location that the return
value of the thread will be stored in. If \fIt\fR is NULL,
\fBqthread_retloc\fR() returns a pointer to the location that the return value
of the currently running thread will be stored in. If the thread's return value
will not be stored via FEBs, this function will return NULL.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
